For some of the more unusual exhibits, check out: 
* Mark Farid's 'Seeing I' exhibition at Watermans, based on a day in the life of four Brentford residents who recorded their lives with a set of digital glasses; 
* Sue Cooper's escapees from a local care home, who are liable to be lounging somewhere around Catherine Wheel Road; 
* and Tom Morley's Art Car, in the shape of a Vauxhall Corsa.
